  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who views their profile. This is intended to protect user privacy and align with Instagram's policies.\n\nBe cautious of third-party apps or services that claim to offer this functionality, as they may not be secure and could potentially compromise your Instagram account or personal data. It's best to use official Instagram features and adhere to their guidelines for privacy and security.\n\nIf you're interested in seeing who interacts with your content, you can check who likes or comments on your posts and who views your Stories; Instagram provides these insights natively within the app.",
